 {"id":"brenner_bot-kpso","title":"Landing Page: Tutorial CTA Integration","description":"# Purpose

Add a prominent call-to-action for the tutorial system on the brennerbot.org landing page. This is the primary discovery mechanism — users should naturally find the tutorial after understanding what BrennerBot is.

---

# Placement Rationale

**Constraint**: No new navbar item (already crowded with Corpus, Distillations, Method, Operators, Glossary, Sessions)

**Solution**: Prominent section on landing page

**Location**: After the WhatIsThis component, before the feature cards grid

**Rationale**:
1. WhatIsThis explains what BrennerBot is
2. Tutorial CTA offers to teach how to USE it
3. Feature cards provide alternatives for exploration
4. This creates a natural funnel: Learn → Apply → Explore

---

# Design Specification

## Visual Treatment

Use success accent color (green) to stand out from the primary/accent colors used elsewhere. This signals "action available" and creates visual hierarchy.

**Card Design**:
\`\`\`
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [AcademicCap Icon]                                             │
│                                                                 │
│  Ready to Apply the Method?                                     │
│  Three learning paths from quick start to multi-agent           │
│  orchestration. Apply Brenner's scientific method to your       │
│  own research questions.                                        │
│                                                                 │
│  [~30 min Quick Start] [Agent-Assisted] [Multi-Agent Cockpit]   │
│                                                                 │
│                                          Start Tutorial →       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
\`\`\`

**Styling Details**:
- Border: border-success/30, hover:border-success/50
- Background: gradient from success/5 via success/10 to primary/5
- Icon: Academic cap or graduation cap, size-14, rounded-2xl
- Title: text-xl font-semibold
- Description: text-muted-foreground
- Badges: variant="outline", text-xs
- CTA: text-success font-medium with arrow icon

---

# Implementation

**File**: apps/web/src/app/page.tsx

**Component** (inline or extracted):
\`\`\`tsx
{/* Tutorial CTA - After WhatIsThis */}
<section className="px-4 sm:px-0 animate-fade-in-up">
  <Link href="/tutorial" className="block group">
    <div className={cn(
      "relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8",
      "border border-success/30 hover:border-success/50",
      "bg-gradient-to-br from-success/5 via-success/10 to-primary/5",
      "shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all"
    )}>
      {/* Background orbs */}
      <div className="absolute top-0 right-0 -mt-4 -mr-4 size-32 bg-success/10 rounded-full blur-3xl" />
      <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 -mb-4 -ml-4 size-24 bg-primary/10 rounded-full blur-3xl" />

      <div className="relative flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-center size-14 rounded-2xl bg-success text-success-foreground shadow-lg">
          <AcademicCapIcon className="size-7" />
        </div>

        <div className="flex-1 space-y-2">
          <h3 className="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">
            Ready to Apply the Method?
          </h3>
          <p className="text-muted-foreground">
            Three learning paths from quick start to multi-agent orchestration. 
            Apply Brenner's scientific method to your own research questions.
          </p>
          <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1">
            <Badge variant="outline" className="text-xs">~30 min Quick Start</Badge>
            <Badge variant="outline" className="text-xs">Agent-Assisted</Badge>
            <Badge variant="outline" className="text-xs">Multi-Agent Cockpit</Badge>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-success font-medium">
          <span>Start Tutorial</span>
          <ArrowRightIcon />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Link>
</section>
\`\`\`

---

# Accessibility

- Link wraps entire card (large touch target)
- Descriptive link text via content
- Focus-visible ring for keyboard nav
- Sufficient color contrast

---

# A/B Testing Consideration (Future)

If analytics show low click-through:
1. Try moving above WhatIsThis
2. Try more urgent copy ("Start now →")
3. Try showing time savings ("Save hours of research setup")

---

# Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Tutorial CTA visible on landing page
- [ ] Positioned after WhatIsThis section
- [ ] Uses success accent color scheme
- [ ] Three path badges visible
- [ ] Link navigates to /tutorial
- [ ] Mobile-responsive design
- [ ] Hover/focus states working
